      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIPPLES NZ (10) has had six weeks off since she ventured to Auckland for a midfield finish in a Group 1 and had been ultra consistent with a string of wins and placings in good company prior. Brave third from a wide barrier in the NSW Oaks two back. She is up to winning this if things go her way from the back row. ALWAYSBJOY NZ (11) tackled Ripples during the NSW Oaks series, coming from a wide barrier to finish 4.7m behind her when placed in the heats before finishing down the track in the final. Tricky draw but she beat some smart male rivals to win when off a let-up at Albion Park last week so looks to be in good order. PERFECTDELIGHT (2) came from a wider barrier to find winning form last start at Menangle and should get her chance from this draw. STRIPES (5) has claims off her Breeders Classic win two back while YIRRADIVA (3) rises in grade but draws well and came from a wide barrier to beat some handy fillies at Bathurst last start.",
